title: Ornamental Panel Inscribed Victoria Augusta
medium: Engraving on off white laid paper
description: Upper part of the print depicts the musical contest between Apollo, playingthe lyre and Marsayas playing the bagpipes. In a narrow relief below, the flaying of Marsyas is depicted. Seated on a pedestal at bottom of the print two satyrs play musical pipes. Image is heavily ornamented with figures.
name: Print
